From: OpenCode <opencode@localhost>
Date: Sat, 4 Jul 2026 06:50:00 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] dwmac-sunxi: enable optional "pclk" (GMAC DMA-bus-master
 clock) to fix silent hang on Radxa Cubie A7S / sun60iw2

On the Radxa Cubie A7S (Allwinner A733 / sun60iw2 SoC), the kernel
hangs completely silently (zero further console output, unrecoverable,
confirmed deterministic across 3+ reboots) immediately after:

  dwmac-sunxi 4500000.ethernet end0: configuring for phy/rgmii link mode

Diagnostic instrumentation inside mainline phylink_start() proved that
phylink_start()/phy_start() complete and return successfully. The hang
occurs later in __stmmac_open(), in the call chain leading to
stmmac_enable_all_dma_irq(), which performs the first genuinely
DMA-engine-facing MMIO register write for this device.

Root cause: the sun60iw2p1.dtsi gmac0 node wires CLK_GMAC0_MBUS (the
GMAC DMA engine's AXI/MBUS bus-master clock, distinct from CLK_GMAC0
which only gates the MAC's APB/register-access side and is already
alive) into the generic "pclk" clock-names slot:

    clocks = <&ccu CLK_GMAC0>, <&ccu CLK_GMAC0_MBUS>,
             <&ccu CLK_GMAC0_PHY>, <&ccu CLK_GMAC_PTP>;
    clock-names = "stmmaceth", "pclk", "phy", "ptp_ref";

Mainline's generic stmmac_pltfr_probe() wrapper (stmmac_platform.c)
normally auto-fetches and clk_prepare_enable()s both "stmmaceth" and
"pclk" before calling stmmac_dvr_probe(). However, this vendor glue
driver (dwmac-sunxi.c) bypasses that wrapper entirely -- it calls
stmmac_probe_config_dt() and stmmac_dvr_probe() directly -- and its
own manual clock-management code only knows about "phy"/"phy25m",
"hsi_ahb", "hsi_axi", and "nsi" (gated behind SUNXI_DWMAC_HSI_CLK_GATE/
SUNXI_DWMAC_NSI_CLK_GATE variant flags). The "pclk" string does not
appear anywhere in dwmac-sunxi.c or dwmac-sunxi.h.

The gmac0_mbus_clk CCU gate itself (drivers/clk/sunxi-ng/ccu-sun60iw2.c,
register 0x05E4 bit 11) is an ordinary SUNXI_CCU_GATE_WITH_KEY with no
CLK_IS_CRITICAL/CLK_IGNORE_UNUSED flags, so it is never turned on by
anyone. The GMAC's DMA engine therefore never receives its bus clock,
and stmmac_enable_all_dma_irq()'s subsequent register write into that
unclocked block stalls the AHB/AXI bus indefinitely -- a genuine
hardware bus hang, not a software deadlock, which is why the freeze
is total and silent (no oops, no RCU-stall/softlockup warning, no
further output on any CPU).

Fix: add an explicit, optional "pclk" clock to struct sunxi_dwmac and
fetch/enable/disable it in sunxi_dwmac_resource_get()/
sunxi_dwmac_clk_init()/sunxi_dwmac_clk_exit(), mirroring the existing
pattern already used for nsi_clk/hsi_ahb/hsi_axi. devm_clk_get_optional()
is used so boards/variants whose DT does not declare a "pclk"
clock-names entry are completely unaffected (returns NULL, not an
error).

---
 bsp/drivers/stmmac/dwmac-sunxi.c | 15 +++++++++++++++
 bsp/drivers/stmmac/dwmac-sunxi.h |  8 ++++++++
 2 files changed, 23 insertions(+)

diff --git a/bsp/drivers/stmmac/dwmac-sunxi.c b/bsp/drivers/stmmac/dwmac-sunxi.c
--- a/bsp/drivers/stmmac/dwmac-sunxi.c
+++ b/bsp/drivers/stmmac/dwmac-sunxi.c
@@ -279,8 +279,19 @@
 		}
 	}

+	if (chip->pclk) {
+		ret = clk_prepare_enable(chip->pclk);
+		if (ret) {
+			sunxi_err(chip->dev, "Enable pclk failed\n");
+			goto err_pclk;
+		}
+	}
+
 	return 0;

+err_pclk:
+	if (chip->soc_phy_clk_en)
+		clk_disable_unprepare(chip->phy_clk);
 err_phy:
 	if (chip->variant->flags & SUNXI_DWMAC_NSI_CLK_GATE)
 		clk_disable_unprepare(chip->nsi_clk);
@@ -299,6 +310,8 @@

 static void sunxi_dwmac_clk_exit(struct sunxi_dwmac *chip)
 {
+	if (chip->pclk)
+		clk_disable_unprepare(chip->pclk);
 	if (chip->soc_phy_clk_en)
 		clk_disable_unprepare(chip->phy_clk);
 	if (chip->variant->flags & SUNXI_DWMAC_NSI_CLK_GATE)
@@ -524,6 +537,17 @@
 		}
 	}

+	/* GMAC DMA-engine bus-master clock (CLK_GMAC0_MBUS on sun60iw2).
+	 * Optional: devm_clk_get_optional() returns NULL (not an error) on
+	 * boards/variants whose DT doesn't declare a "pclk" clock-names slot,
+	 * so existing dwmac-sunxi.c consumers without this clock are unaffected.
+	 */
+	chip->pclk = devm_clk_get_optional(dev, "pclk");
+	if (IS_ERR(chip->pclk)) {
+		sunxi_err(dev, "Get pclk clk failed\n");
+		return -EINVAL;
+	}
+
 #if (LINUX_VERSION_CODE >= KERNEL_VERSION(5, 15, 0))
 	if (chip->variant->flags & SUNXI_DWMAC_MEM_ECC) {
 		sunxi_info(dev, "Support mem ecc\n");

diff --git a/bsp/drivers/stmmac/dwmac-sunxi.h b/bsp/drivers/stmmac/dwmac-sunxi.h
--- a/bsp/drivers/stmmac/dwmac-sunxi.h
+++ b/bsp/drivers/stmmac/dwmac-sunxi.h
@@ -153,6 +153,14 @@
 	struct clk *nsi_clk;
 	struct clk *hsi_ahb;
 	struct clk *hsi_axi;
+	struct clk *pclk; /* GMAC DMA-engine bus-master clock (CLK_GMAC0_MBUS on sun60iw2);
+			    * mainline stmmac_pltfr_probe() normally auto-enables the DT
+			    * "pclk" clock-names slot, but this driver bypasses that
+			    * wrapper (calls stmmac_probe_config_dt()+stmmac_dvr_probe()
+			    * directly), so it must be fetched/enabled explicitly here
+			    * or the DMA engine's bus clock stays gated and the very
+			    * first DMA-facing MMIO access (stmmac_enable_all_dma_irq(),
+			    * from ndo_open()) hangs the AHB/AXI bus indefinitely. */
 	struct reset_control *ahb_rst;
 	struct reset_control *hsi_rst;
 	struct device *dev;
--
2.43.0
